column1: #Text=The Oklahoma City Thunder ( 50 - 22 ) defeated the visiting Utah Jazz ( 35 - 37 ) 113 - 91 , on Friday night at Chesapeake Energy Arena .
#Text=This game was tight throughout the first half , but the Thunder came out strong in the third quarter , out - scoring the Jazz 29 - 8 .

#Text=The Jazz came out strong in the third quarter , out - scoring the Jazz 29 - 8 , but the Thunder battled back in the second and third quarters , where they out - scored the Jazz 59 - 42 , to tie the game on a 24 - 2 run .

column6: The Thunder led the entire game[1]
The Thunder led the entire game[1]

column1: #Text=Oklahoma City was led by Russell Westbrook , who scored a game - high 15 points ( 6 - 15 FG , 1 - 3 3Pt , 2 - 3 FT ) , along with nine assists , seven rebounds and three steals , in 27 minutes .

column6: did not lead team in scoring

column1: #Text=Kevin Durant followed up with 20 points ( 7 - 11 FG , 2 - 4 3Pt , 4 - 5 FT ) , eight rebounds , nine assists , two steals and one block , in 30 minutes , while Dion Waiters chipped in 17 points ( 8 - 16 FG , 1 - 4 3Pt ) , two rebounds , three assists and three steals , in 29 minutes .

#Text=Gordon Hayward had six points ( 2 - 6 FG , 0 - 3 3Pt , 2 - 2 FT ) , five assists and two rebounds , while Derrick Favors chipped in seven points ( 3 - 8 FG , 1 - 4 3Pt ) , two rebounds , three assists and three steals , in 29 minutes .
#Text=The Jazz had six players score in double figures , including Gordon Hayward .
